messages.message: @Serena yes. Reindexing is only triggered for very old docs (or) for documents with missing ibdocs. In this scenario, it shouldn’t have triggered any re-indexing. Let me check if the job actually triggered .

• after the document digitized (which took unexpectedly long for this short doc, around 30s)
• when i ran a field on this doc, i see `Found 1 document(s) to re-index.`in the logs after the `/extraction` API call was received in `api-server`
+1 upload also seems to be taking a long time as well.
